{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"alias":"unfeared-infirm-marmot","creation_channel":"cli","description":"## Why\nDeferred from b550 (GitHub Actions naming cleanup). gerrit-verify.yaml's build-and-test job HAND-COPIES test.yml's matrix + gate steps; tests/unit/test_ci_workflow_parity.py exists solely to police that the two copies stay in sync. This duplication could be factored into a reusable workflow_call (the pattern _optionality.yml already uses), with checkout parameterized by gerrit-refspec (branch-head for the mirror lane, exact patchset for the Verified gate).\n\n## Risk / why it's separate\ngerrit-verify.yaml is the SOLE Verified-vote gate — high blast radius. Must be its own independently-reviewed Gerrit change, not bundled with cosmetic renames. Replacing the parity test removes a safety property (two independent copies); confirm the reusable-workflow approach is acceptable before implementing.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Shared build-and-test steps live in a single reusable workflow_call file (e.g. _build-and-test.yml), invoked by both test.yml (branch head) and gerrit-verify.yaml (patchset).\n- [ ] The Verified vote still works end-to-end (a real gerrit-verify dispatch casts Verified +1).\n- [ ] test_ci_workflow_parity.py updated or retired coherently with the new structure.\n- [ ] make lint + tests pass; lands through Gerrit with both votes.","id":"2b60-0b39-39ff-47ea","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"Consolidate test.yml + gerrit-verify build-and-test into a reusable workflow"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784441283290238001,"uuid":"3dd41426-f51c-4974-bd15-c1e89fb36dbb"}